%N A395920 Number of relations R on an n-element set such that the transitive closure of R has exactly three elements more than R.
%H A395920 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transitive_closure">Transitive closure</a>
%e A395920 For n=0,1 the only relation is transitive (or has no missing pair to add), so a(0) = a(1) = 0.
